    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 362.11/5334</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 30, 9.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3499. Legation’s 3469, May 25.<note n="1" xml:id="d103fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    Certificate from Embassy’s doctor, optical division, at Jaryour [<hi
                        rend="italic">sic</hi>], states in case of Corpl. <persName>Edward
                        Roberts</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Right eye entirely gone, left eye partially saved by hasty operation so
                            that <persName>Roberts</persName> can now distinguish moving objects and
                            persons. He is out of bed and in good health. To be given education for
                            blind.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>As certificate states <persName>Roberts</persName> subject for repatriation, have
                    asked Spanish Embassy, Berlin, to take steps to secure repatriation, although no
                    agreement yet exists between two Governments. This only one case of several
                    which are eligible for immediate repatriation. Recommend agreement this subject
                    be arranged at the earliest practical moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
